 highlight the social implications of traumatic history.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Mrz 2024) 0aDenkmal für die ermordeten Juden Europas (Berlin, Germany). 0aHolocaust memorials. 0aHolocaust, Jewish (1939-1945)xHistoriography. 0aHolocaust, Jewish (1939-1945)zGermanyxInfluence. 0aPsychoanalysis and culture. 4aArea Studies : German Studies. 4aCultural Studies : Cultural Studies. 4aHistory : History. 4aHistory : Holocaust Studies. 4aJewish Studies : Jewish Studies. 4aLiterature : Comparative Literature. 7aHISTORY / Holocaust.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013z978311148737340uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780791477779?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780791477779423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780791477779/original  a978-3-11-148737-3  SUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles